postcontent: BEAUTIFUL Remington 788 carbine in .243 Winchester caliber!  Includes one detachable magazine, Weaver rings and bases and a 3x9 scope.  Bore is bright and shiny with sharp rifling.  Wood is in excellent condition with rarely seen figure. Stock has never been cut - has original Remington buttplate.  Bluing is very good with thin spots on the barrel from where it rested in the cabinet. Scope is in great condition with clear glass and a very sharp image.The 788 was Remington's economy model (you'll notice there is no checkering on the stock).
